  Privacy Act Officer : Business Actor

The Privacy Act requires agencies to have at least one person who fulfils the role of a privacy officer. A privacy officer must be familiar with the privacy principles in the Privacy Act, work to make sure the agency complies with the Privacy Act, deal with any complaints from the agency's clients about possible breaches of privacy, deal with requests for access to personal information, or correction of personal information, and act as the agency’s liaison.

  NIH OPERA : Business Actor

  Board of Scientific Advisors (BSA) : Business Actor

Makes recommendations on research priorities conducted or supported by the Institute. This includes the evaluation of NCI awarded grants, cooperative agreements and contracts and concept review of those activities which it considers meritorious and consistent with the Institute's programs

Evaluate the bids on their ability to meet the requirements as stated in the RFP. It does NOT include an evaluation of price

  Business Tasks : Grouping
  Close Contract : Business Role

Perform all necessary steps to close out a contract, either at the end of the Period of Performance, or at termination of the contract

  Evaluate Contractor : Business Role

Evaluate the contractor's performance in providing the products/services specified in the contract

  Deliver Deliverables : Business Role

Deliver the artifacts, products and/pr services as specified in the contract

  Close Out Contract : Business Function
  Contract Admistration : Business Function

Includes evaluating contractor performance, reviewing  individual subcontractor reports, approving invoices and authorizing payments, reviewing deliverables, directing the contractor, coordinate with the COR

  Evaluate Deliverables : Business Role

Gather and evaluate all vendor deliverables against the agreed-upon acceptance criteria

  Deliver Requirements : Business Role

Deliver the services and products as specified on the contract

  Execute Contract : Business Role

Sign the contract and perform all necessary steps to make it legally binding

  Notify and Debrief Unsuccessful Offerors : Business Role

Notify the bidders that did not win the contract and debrief them on why they were not selected

  Award Contract : Business Function
  Conduct Responsibility and Legal Reviews : Business Role

Conduct reviews to ensure that the acquisition follows all laws, regulations, rules, processes and procedures

  Determine Best Value : Business Role

Determine the best value by comparing the price and ability to meet RFP requirements of all bids and selecting the one with the best value

  Revise Final Proposal : Business Role

Make any changes to the final RFP bid

  Conduct Discussions and Negations : Business Role

Negotiate price and other conditions with selected bidders as part of source selection

  Conduct Selection Process : Business Function 		Open negotiations, have exchanges with offerors, request final quote revisions, conduct past performance evaluation. COR provides source selection recommendation based on final proposals and quotes. CO writes a source selection documentation (FAR Part 15 and 16) or basis of award document (FAR Part 8).

  Develop Acquisition Plan : Business Function

Contract Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS) where the Assessing Official Representatives (the CORs), enter evaluations based upon contractor performance and once reviewed by the Assessing Official (CO), the evaluation is shared with the contractor for comment. https://www.cpars.gov/

  Requiring Office : Business Actor

The office requesting the acquisition, write the SOW, IGCE/IGE, technical evaluation factors

  Peer Reviewer : Business Actor 		Review R&D proposal and determine technical acceptability and score proposals as part of the technical evaluation panel
  Office of Space and Facilities Management (OSFM) : Business Actor

  Coordinates NCI acquisitions for space and facilities

  Office of Small and Disadvantaged Business Utilization (OSDBU) : Business Actor

Reviews to ensure appropriate consideration has been made to small and disadvantaged businesses in the acquisition process

  NIH Office of Financial Management : Business Actor

Provides financial review and oversight post award

  NIH Government Property Administrator : Business Actor

Advises staff on, reviews and coordinates the acquisition, loan, transfer and disposal of accountable property items per HHS and NIH property regulations and procedure, and the NIH acquisition and property management processes pre- and post award

  Ethics Consultation : Business Role
  Foreign Clearance (FACTS) : Business Actor

If the prime or subcontractor is a foreign entity, reviews for compliance

  EEO Clearance : Business Actor

The National Pre-Award Registry (website) provides information concerning Federal Contractors, that have been reviewed by the Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs (OFCCP). These Federal Contractors have been found to be "In Compliance" with the Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) regulations that the OFCCP is mandated to enforce. The information contained in this Registry is for a past two-year period from today. The Registry is updated nightly and facilities reviewed more than 2 years ago are removed as new ones are added. The CO goes to the Department of Labor region where the offeror is based to confirm that the successful awardee is in compliance with EEO laws. https://www.eeoc.gov/

  Determine Acquisition Strategy : Business Role 		Determine whether it is a new requirement or existing. Determine the budget. Conduct market research. Communicate with the CO, COR, and budget office. Determining contracting approach, and contract type. Determining needs, conduct benefits analysis. Consider technology issues. Determine liability issues. Consider alternate, existing contract mechanisms. Determine milestone schedule.
  Obtain Funding : Business Role

Obtaining the necessary funds to pay for the services/products included in the RFP over the full lifetime of the contract

  Conduct Market Research : Business Role

Researching the market for similar services or products, different ways of meeting the requirements, what companies can deliver these, etc.

  Define Requirements : Business Role

Define the requirements to be included in a Request for Proposal (RFP) and which a vendor will need to deliver and adhere to. This could include detailed services, products, etc.
